717589f-b.title: Manhattan: Broadway - 58th Street (West)
717589f-b.text:
Broadway, east side, north from W. 58th to 59th Street,
showing a two-story taxpayer that is to be demolished. Thts
site, an Ehret property is to be improved with two distinctive
apartment houses. A full account is to be found in the Her-
ald Tribune of January 21, 1940. View 2 is limited to this
block front. Central Park West is at the left of the extensive
pfeceding view. There upon appears the Mcyflower (61st to
62nd Streets) and the twin-towered Century Apartments(68nd to
63rd Streets).
May 21, 1939
Views 1,2
P. L. Sperr
NO REPRODUCTIONS
